Thanks for the clean up Patrick!
How were these decided to be manually disabled? Were these fixed manually (and these couldn't be solved easily)?
The warning SC2034 is "variable is unused" because `fiu` is unused here.  I couldn't tell an obviously better way to fix this.
Gotcha thanks

Could just do something like:

```
if [ -z "$KERNEL_SYSFS_FIU"/*.fiu ]; then
  KERNEL_FIU_ID="c0000000.spi"
else
  KERNEL_FIU_ID="c0000000.fiu"
fi
```

(also note that the code in the shellcheck disable in bios-update.sh is doing the exact same thing in a different way)

We can also fix that up later though
